        I frequently led sections, serving as both first and second in command on multiple occasions. 
        This responsibility built a strong sense of accountability and equipped me with resilience and determination. 
        Delivering lessons on drill and navigation to new recruits allowed me to step into the role of a teacher and mentor, enhancing my communication skills and confidence. 
        <br>
        <br>
        The core values of the Army Cadet Force became more than just words; they shaped my character and approach to challenges. 
        Operating under pressure in harsh environments, especially during night patrols and ambushes, required quick thinking and strategic decision-making. 
        These situations heightened my problem-solving skills and taught me how to maintain composure in dynamic environments. 
        Collaborating with individuals Iâ€™ve never met before, enriched my understanding of teamwork and the necessity of clear communication to achieve common goals.
        <br>
        <br>
        The discipline ingrained in me ensured that I adhered to high standards, whether it was through meticulous uniform maintenance or upholding the strict moral code. 
        These experiences emphasized the importance of doing everything to a high standard to prevent mistakes.
        <br>
        <br>
        In reflection, my journey with the Army Cadet Force prepared me well for future challenges. 
        The skills I developed, the responsibilities I shouldered, and the relationships I built have left an incredible mark on me. 
        I emerged sharper, more confident, and ready to face whatever lies ahead.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
